## §2 Determinism mode per stage

### bytes-identical (default; preferred when achievable)

Stage produces byte-stable output given identical input + frozen substrate paths. Regression test: SHA256 of stage output matches SHA256 of canonical fixture run-by-run. Failure = block-mode; investigate fixture drift OR substrate edit.

**Strategy for image bytes** (encoder metadata): EITHER strip encoder metadata post-write (`--strip-metadata` flag in encoder config) OR disable encoder timestamps at write-time (`tIME` chunk omission for PNG, EXIF stripping for JPEG). Per-stage: declare which strategy is in force.

### field-masked-hash (when bytes-identical not achievable)

Stage produces output whose bytes vary across runs at declared-nondeterministic fields, but content is otherwise identical. Regression test: SHA256 of output AFTER masking declared-nondeterministic fields matches canonical fixture. Failure = block-mode; investigate which masked-out field changed (telemetry signal, possibly SR-T2 fixture-staleness).

